<p>
          <img src="pkiteam.jpg" align="right" alt="PKI/Trust Team, Summer 2004" width="280" height="193"> <p><a href="http://www.cs.dartmouth.edu/%7Epkilab/"><b>Dartmouth PKI/Trust Lab</b></a><br>S.W. Smith, Principal Investigator</p><h4>Objective:</h4>Public key cryptography enables robust expression of non-trivial,compound statements and beliefs, among entities that share no commonsecrets (something very important to the emerging distributed informationworld).<p>The Dartmouth PKI/Trust Lab seeks to examine---both as abstract research aswell as concrete proof-of-concept---selected areas where "missingpieces" in the public key infrastructure prevent this tool from fullyaddressing these trust issues.</p><ul>  <li> <a href="#papers"></a><a href="#papers"><b>Papers</b></a> </li>  <li> <a href="#theses"><b>Student Theses</b></a></li> </ul><a name="papers" class="style1">&nbsp;</a><table  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">  <tr bgcolor="#005500">    <td height="7" colspan="5"></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td width="7" rowspan="75" align="right" valign="top" bgcolor="#005500"> </td>    <td width="1" rowspan="75" align="right" valign="top"></td>    <td height="7"></td>    <td width="1" rowspan="75" align="left" valign="top"></td>    <td width="7" rowspan="75" align="left" valign="top"bgcolor="#005500"></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><span class="style5">Papers</span></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td height="2" bgcolor="#005500"></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><span class="style4"><br>      S.W. Smith.<br>      <a href="http://www.springeronline.com/sgw/cda/frontpage/0,11855,4-102-22-36520721-0,00.html?changeHeader=true"><cite>Trusted Computing Platforms: Design and Applications.</cite></a><br>Springer. To appear, December 2004 or January 2005. <br>    </span></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td height="2" bgcolor="#005500"></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><span class="style4"><br>      A. Iliev, S.W. Smith. <br>"Enhancing User Privacy via Trusted Compu